com.ibm.team.build.ant.task

Class WaitForTeamBuildTask

  • java.lang.Object
    • Task
      • com.ibm.team.build.ant.task.AbstractTeamBuildTask
        • com.ibm.team.build.ant.task.WaitForTeamBuildTask
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IStaticReset

    public class WaitForTeamBuildTask
extends AbstractTeamBuildTask
    Ant task used to wait for a build to enter a specified build state.

    Required attributes are:

    Note: Only one of the two below is required in any given invocation of the task. They are mutually exclusively.

    • requestUUID - The UUID of the build request that should be waited on.
    • buildResultUUID - The UUID of the build result that should be waited on.

    Optional attribute are:

    • statesToWaitFor - A comma separated list of build state names. Valid values are:
      • NOT_STARTED - A build that has been requested but has not been started. Also commonly known as pending.
      • IN_PROGRESS - The build is currently in progress.
      • COMPLETED - The build completed normally but may have failures.
      • CANCELED - The request for the build has been canceled before it ever had a chance to start.
      • INCOMPLETE - The build was not completed normally. Also commonly known as abandoned.
      It defaults to the states of COMPLETED and INCOMPLETE
    • timeout - The maximum amount in seconds the task should wait on the build. It must be greater than zero. The default is to wait forever.
    • interval - The time in seconds between checking to determine if the build has entered the desired state. It must be greater than zero and less than or equal to the timeout value. The default is to check every 30 seconds.
    • buildStateProperty - The property to write the state of the build when the task finishes waiting. It will only be set if the build entered one of the specified states to wait for.
    • buildStatusProperty - The property to write the status of the build when the task finishes waiting.

    See AbstractTeamBuildTask for additional required and optional attributes.

    Since:
    0.6
